---
import TextLayout from "../layouts/TextLayout.astro";
---

<TextLayout title="Terms and Conditions" noindex={true}>
  <div class="content-container-alt">
    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>
      These Terms and Conditions govern the use of the online ticket store
      operated by the Open Home Foundation (hereinafter referred to as 'we',
      'our', or 'us'). By placing an order through our website at
      <a href="events.openhomefoundation.org">events.openhomefoundation.org</a> or
      its embedded version at
      <a href="sotoh.openhomefoundation.org">sotoh.openhomefoundation.org</a>,
      you agree to be bound by these Terms and Conditions. Please read them
      carefully before placing any order.
    </p>

    <h2>Eligibility</h2>
    <p>
      You must be at least 18 years old and legally capable of entering into
      binding contracts to place orders on our online ticket store.
    </p>

    <h2>Orders and Features of Events</h2>
    <p>
      When you click the "Order now" button on our website, a contract for the
      participation in the selected event is concluded between you and the Open
      Home Foundation, Grabenstrasse 25, 6340 Baar, Switzerland, Email:
      <a href="mailto:hello@openhomefoundation.org"
        >hello@openhomefoundation.org</a
      >.
    </p>
    <p>
      All tickets displayed on our website are subject to availability. We
      reserve the right to limit the number of tickets per order and to refuse
      or cancel any order at our discretion. The information on the website
      (descriptions, images and other features) are only to be understood as
      approximate representations and do not represent any warranty or guarantee
      of specific features of an event, unless they are expressly designated in
      writing as binding.
    </p>
    <p>
      Participation in an event may be subject to specific rules, requirements
      or instructions issued, which must be complied with by participants.
      Failure to comply with such rules may result in exclusion from the event,
      without any entitlement to a refund, to the extent permitted by applicable
      law.
    </p>

    <h2>Pricing and Payment</h2>
    <p>
      For events where participation is paid, all prices are listed in the
      applicable currency and include taxes where required by law. Prices may be
      amended without notice. Payment must be made using the methods specified
      on our website. We reserve the right to correct any pricing errors before
      or after an order is placed.
    </p>

    <h2>Delivery, Form of Ticket and Event Access</h2>
    <p>
      Tickets are delivered electronically after successful completion of the
      order process, in particular by email or by making them available for
      download or access on the website. Electronic tickets may, in particular,
      be issued in the form of a unique access code (e.g. QR code or
      alphanumeric code) that entitles the holder to participate in or access
      the event. No identity check is carried out by us at the time of access or
      participation. We are therefore entitled to grant access to the event to
      any person who presents or submits a valid access code and shall be deemed
      to have duly fulfilled our contractual obligations once access to the
      event has been granted on the basis of such code. You are responsible for
      keeping the access code secure and preventing unauthorised use. Any misuse
      of the access code, including use by third parties, shall be at your risk.
    </p>

    <h2>Withdrawal</h2>
    <h3>No Right of withdrawal for certain contracts</h3>
    <p>
      In accordance with the relevant regulations within the European Union,
      which might be applicable, there is no right of withdrawal for services
      related to leisure activities if the contract provides for a specific date
      or period of performance. Furthermore, the right of withdrawal expires
      prematurely if we have provided the service in full with your prior
      express consent and you have simultaneously confirmed your knowledge that
      you lose your right of withdrawal upon complete fulfilment of the
      contract; for digital content not provided on a physical data carrier, it
      expires if we have begun execution with your express consent before the
      expiry of the withdrawal period and you have confirmed your knowledge that
      you thereby lose your right of withdrawal.
    </p>

    <h3>Right of withdrawal for other contracts</h3>
    <p>
      You have the right to withdraw from any contract concluded on the online
      ticket store of Open Home Foundation within fourteen (14) days without
      giving any reason. The withdrawal period begins on the day of the
      conclusion of the contract.
    </p>
    <p>
      To exercise your right of withdrawal, you must inform us of your decision
      to withdraw from the contract by means of a clear statement (e.g., a
      letter sent by post or an email). You can contact us at:
    </p>
    <p>
      The Open Home Foundation<br />
      Grabenstrasse 25<br />
      6340 Baar<br />
      Switzerland<br />
      Email: <a href="mailto:hello@openhomefoundation.org"
        >hello@openhomefoundation.org</a
      >
    </p>
    <p>
      You may use the below model withdrawal form, but this is not mandatory.
    </p>
    <p>
      To meet the withdrawal deadline, it is sufficient for you to send your
      notification of exercising your right of withdrawal before the withdrawal
      period expires.
    </p>

    <h3>Effects of withdrawal</h3>
    <p>
      We will refund all payments received from you without undue delay and at
      the latest within fourteen days from the day we receive your notice of
      your withdrawal from the contract. We will use the same means of payment
      for this refund as you used for the original transaction, unless expressly
      agreed otherwise with you. You will not be charged for this refund.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you have requested that the services commence during the withdrawal
      period, you shall be required to pay us an appropriate amount
      corresponding to the proportion of the services already provided up to the
      time at which you notify us of the exercise of your right of withdrawal in
      respect of this contract, relative to the total scope of the services
      provided for under the contract.
    </p>

    <h3>Model withdrawal form (optional)</h3>
    <p>
      <em
        >(If you wish to cancel the contract, please complete this form and
        return it.)</em
      >
    </p>
    <p>
      To: The Open Home Foundation, Grabenstrasse 25, 6340 Baar, Switzerland
    </p>
    <p>
      I/we(*) hereby cancel the contract concluded by me/us(*) for the purchase
      of the following goods (*)/ for the provision of the following services
      (*):
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Ordered on (*) /received on (*):</li>
      <li>Name of customer(s):</li>
      <li>Address of customer(s):</li>
      <li>Signature of purchaser(s) (only for paper notifications):</li>
      <li>Date:</li>
    </ul>
    <p>(*) Delete as appropriate.</p>

    <h2>Cancellation or Postponement of Events</h2>
    <p>
      We reserve the right to cancel or postpone an event for material reasons.
      In the event of cancellation of an event, the ticket price paid for the
      affected event shall be refunded to you without undue delay, unless the
      cancellation is due to an event of force majeure. In the event of a
      postponement, your ticket shall remain valid for the rescheduled date. If
      you are unable to attend the event on the new date, you may request a
      refund of the ticket price, unless the postponement is due to an event of
      force majeure.
    </p>
    <p>
      For the purposes of these Terms, force majeure means any event beyond our
      reasonable control which could not have been foreseen or avoided even with
      due care, including in particular natural disasters, epidemics or
      pandemics, acts of government or authorities, war, terrorism, civil
      unrest, strikes, or failures of public utilities or telecommunications
      networks.
    </p>
    <p>
      Any further claims, in particular claims for compensation of travel,
      accommodation or other ancillary costs, are excluded to the extent
      permitted by applicable law.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact Form</h2>
    <p>
      You are responsible for ensuring that any information or input you provide
      to the Open Home Foundation, whether through the contact form on the
      website or otherwise, is, to the best of your knowledge, accurate and
      relevant. Unless otherwise agreed, the Open Home Foundation may rely on
      such information without independent verification. While we will do our
      best to respond to queries and comments sent through the contact form on
      the website, communications via the contact form do not constitute formal
      notice to the Open Home Foundation.
    </p>

    <h2>Intellectual Property</h2>
    <p>
      Unless otherwise stated, all content on our website at
      <a href="events.openhomefoundation.org">events.openhomefoundation.org</a> or
      its embedded version at
      <a href="sotoh.openhomefoundation.org">sotoh.openhomefoundation.org</a>,
      including images, logos, and text, is the property of the Open Home
      Foundation and protected by intellectual property laws. You may not use,
      reproduce, or distribute any content without prior written permission of
      the Open Home Foundation.
    </p>

    <h2>Privacy</h2>
    <p>
      Your personal data will be processed in accordance with our Privacy
      Policy, which is available <a href="/privacy-policy/">here</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
    <p>
      To the maximum extent permitted by law, we exclude all liability for any
      indirect or consequential damages arising from your use of our online
      shop. Our total liability shall not exceed the amount paid for the ordered
      items.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you are a consumer (i.e. purchasing goods for purposes outside your
      trade, business or profession), nothing in these Terms and Conditions
      limits your non-waivable statutory rights under the law of your country of
      delivery.
    </p>

    <h2>Governing Law and Jurisdiction</h2>
    <p>
      These Terms and Conditions shall be governed by and construed in
      accordance with the laws of Switzerland, excluding its conflict of law
      provisions and the UNCITRAL convention on the international sale of goods.
      Any disputes shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the
      competent courts in the Canton of Zug, Switzerland.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to Terms</h2>
    <p>
      We reserve the right to amend these Terms and Conditions at any time.
      Changes will be effective upon posting on our website. It is your
      responsibility to review these Terms periodically.
    </p>
    <p>
      If any provision of these Terms and Conditions is found to be invalid,
      this shall not affect the validity of the remaining provisions or the
      Terms and Conditions as a whole.
    </p>

    <h2>Effective Date</h2>
    <p>These Terms and Conditions were last updated on 2025-12-19.</p>
  </div>
</TextLayout>

<style lang="scss">
  .content-container-alt {
    h1,
    .h1,
    h2,
    .h2,
    h3,
    .h3,
    p,
    ul,
    ol {
      color: var(--text-on-light);
    }

    h2 {
      margin-top: 2.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    h3 {
      margin-top: 2rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
      font-weight: 500;
      font-size: clamp(1.125rem, 0.9886rem + 0.6818vw, 1.5rem);
    }

    p {
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      line-height: 1.7;
      text-wrap: auto;
    }

    ul {
      list-style-type: disc;
    }

    ul,
    ol {
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      padding-left: 1rem;
      font-size: 1.125rem;
      font-weight: 300;

      li {
        margin-bottom: 0;
        line-height: 1.7;
      }
    }

    a {
      color: var(--ohf-blue);
      text-decoration: underline;

      &:hover {
        text-decoration: none;
      }
    }
  }
</style>
